Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.07,0:00:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the last entry...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.41,0:00:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Starswirl's final words\Nbefore he vanished!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.21,0:00:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Applejack: All those legendary\Nponies were real too?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.98,0:00:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And then NONE of them were\Never heard from again?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.52,0:00:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Twilight: They used their magic to\Nopen a portal to limbo
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.35,0:00:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} We need to find items{\i0}\N{\i1} that are connected{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.25,0:00:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} to the pillars in some way.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.22,0:00:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We brought you back!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.49,0:00:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot bring ONLY\Nthe pillars back!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.11,0:01:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Your pitiful attempt\Nto imprison me
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.14,0:01:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,has FAILED, Starswirl!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.81,0:01:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You must return us to limbo.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.78,0:01:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the only way to stop him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.72,0:01:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I only figured out\Nhow to bring you back.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.95,0:01:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Working on it..
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.96,0:01:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,No table of contents..
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.66,0:01:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Allow me to assist.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.37,0:01:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.37,0:01:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the power of Ponehenge,\Nyour banishing spell is useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.58,0:01:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You have studied my writings.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.31,0:01:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Surely you have some other plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.51,0:01:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,No... I just wanted to save\Nyou, I didn't think--
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.45,0:01:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't fret.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.45,0:02:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,When I extinguish the light and\Nhope of this miserable world,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.09,0:02:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,you won't remember any of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.09,0:02:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.29,0:02:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This one is almost.. as\Nstrong as you, Starswirl.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.03,0:02:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But even in my weakened state,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.73,0:02:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,she cannot stop the\Nmight of shadows!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.67,0:02:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucky for her,\Nshe's not alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.91,0:02:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,ARRGGGHHH!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.28,0:02:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Know this, fiend.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.08,0:02:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We will not rest until we find\Na way to return you to limbo.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.82,0:02:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Never!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.96,0:02:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Your days of glory are\Nthrough, Starswirl.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.63,0:02:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Now my dark power will reign\Nand you six will bow to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.70,0:02:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, where'd he go?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.14,0:02:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a riddle\Nwe must unravel.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.24,0:02:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.31,0:02:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,How long have we been gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.44,0:02:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Over a thousand years.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.54,0:03:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Then my spell worked... before\Nit was meddled with.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.78,0:03:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And the realm has been at\Npeace for a millennia!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.72,0:03:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we did have to save\Neverypony from Nightmare Moon
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.22,0:03:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and Discord and Chrysalis and\NKing Sombra and Lord Tirek and
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.39,0:03:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,there was that one time when\NStarlight traveled through time
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.26,0:03:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and almost destroyed\Nlife as we know it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.36,0:03:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's all in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.73,0:03:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are truly\Nthis accomplished,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.93,0:03:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,we will stop the Pony of\NShadows twice as fast together.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.57,0:03:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We shall see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.14,0:03:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It is an easy thing to say\Nyou have saved the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.74,0:03:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It is quite another to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.94,0:03:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we've saved\Nthe world, beardo.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.11,0:03:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can do it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.78,0:03:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Be that as it may, the problem\Nof locating the Pony of Shadows
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.85,0:03:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,remains and this land is vast.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.32,0:03:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It sounds like you need a map.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.39,0:03:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Luckily, we have just the thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.36,0:03:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Something about this\Nmagic seems familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.30,0:03:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you know he\Ncould do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.11,0:04:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He's Starswirl!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.11,0:04:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He can do anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.04,0:04:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This map and, indeed, this very\Ncastle are grown from the seed
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.11,0:04:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,we planted over a\Nthousand years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.92,0:04:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it did work!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.49,0:04:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What worked?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.39,0:04:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Each of us infused a crystal\Nseed with our magic
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.89,0:04:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,in hopes that it would grow\Ninto a force for good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.09,0:04:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We wanted to leave something\Nto protect the realm in our absence,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.30,0:04:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,but we never dreamed our gift\Nwould become so powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.10,0:04:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Y'all mean the\Nelements came from you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.37,0:04:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the sparkly\Ncrystal things that grow
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.41,0:04:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,from the Tree of Harmony\Nand represent each of us?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.18,0:04:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Laughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.95,0:04:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Honesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.98,0:04:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Generosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.15,0:04:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Loyalty.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.08,0:04:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Kindness.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.12,0:04:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And magic!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.25,0:04:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,They are reflections of our own\Nelements of hope, strength,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.82,0:04:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,beauty, bravery,\Nhealing and sorcery.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.96,0:05:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We had no idea our\Nsmall seed would bloom
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.63,0:05:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,into the living\Nspirit of the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.14,0:05:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I am glad our mantles have\Npassed to such capable ponies.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.44,0:05:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,More importantly, we\Nno longer need Ponhenge
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.01,0:05:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to send our foe\Nback to limbo.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.55,0:05:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We can use the stored magic in\Nthis "Tree of Harmony."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.85,0:05:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But doesn't a banishing spell\Ntake a lot of power?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.72,0:05:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd have to sacrifice\Nthe elements for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.09,0:05:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.06,0:05:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,They'd be gone...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.93,0:05:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Forever?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.09,0:05:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Starswirl, I don't think\Nthe Tree can survive
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.80,0:05:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,without the elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.93,0:05:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If it dies, Equestria\Nwill suffer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.70,0:05:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,If the Pony of Shadows has his\Nway, your land will not exist!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.07,0:05:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So unless you have\Na better idea...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.61,0:05:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Our foe will seek dark places\Nfrom which to draw power.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.19,0:05:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I will prepare my spell,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.35,0:05:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we may strike as\Nsoon as you find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.39,0:05:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What are we waiting for?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.96,0:05:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I like your spirit!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.76,0:06:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh huh! Oh yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.20,0:06:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What about\Nthis one?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.84,0:06:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Sea Pony etiquette isn't going\Nto help right now, Spike.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.21,0:06:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, Twilight?\NAre you OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.24,0:06:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I just unleashed ultimate\Nevil and doomed Equestria
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.95,0:06:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,because I was obsessed\Nwith meeting my idol!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.81,0:06:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Why wouldn't I be OK!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.22,0:06:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Pfft. You didn't know that\Nwas gonna happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.65,0:06:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But I should have listened to\Nyou and left things alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.89,0:06:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the elements of harmony\Nwill be lost to fix my mistake!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.19,0:06:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe there's another way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.03,0:06:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If there is, Twilight\Nwill find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.36,0:06:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Portal gate... portal keys...\Nportal spells.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.97,0:06:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,YES! If the Pillars can hold\Nopen the gateway to limbo,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.97,0:06:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,a powerful pony can do the\Nbanishing spell herself!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.74,0:06:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know what this means!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.17,0:06:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,[pant] I can stop carrying books?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.18,0:06:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pillars don't have\Nto leave Equestria!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.51,0:06:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though we'll\Nlose the elements,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.91,0:06:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll have the ponies\Nthat created them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.72,0:06:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Pony of shadows\Nwill be banished for good!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.69,0:07:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That's.. great. Heh.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.79,0:07:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was thinking\Nof another way
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.06,0:07:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that maybe doesn't involve\N"banishing" at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.73,0:07:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Starswirl knew what he was\Ndoing when he cast that spell.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.73,0:07:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,If I can make it\Neven better,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.13,0:07:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe he'll see that I take\Nmagic as seriously as he does.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.17,0:07:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems the dark places
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.71,0:07:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Starswirl indicated on\Nthe map have changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.61,0:07:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet the Pony of Shadows
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.08,0:07:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,would've loved the\NGhastly Caverns
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.62,0:07:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,before 1000\Nyears of erosion
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.72,0:07:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,turned it into the\NGhastly Gorge.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.69,0:07:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The "Appeloosian Wastes" sure\Nsounded dark and desolate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.72,0:07:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knew they would become
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.72,0:07:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,such a popular square\Ndancing destination?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.06,0:07:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And I get how this\Npart of Equestria
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.23,0:07:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,used to be cast\Nin eternal night
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.30,0:07:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,where the Pony of Shadows could\Ndraw power and wreak havoc
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.97,0:07:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,while ponies were powerless\Nto stop him, but,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.27,0:07:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,IT'S KINDA MADE A COMEBACK.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.77,0:07:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,DID I MENTION IT'S\NREALLY BRIGHT?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.31,0:08:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems there are fewer dark\Ncorners in the realm these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.68,0:08:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that a good thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.39,0:08:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,True. The Pony of Shadows\Nwill have a hard time
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.22,0:08:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,regaining power.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.42,0:08:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,When he rears his\Nhead, we'll be ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.16,0:08:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't there some way to banish\Nhim without losing all of you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.70,0:08:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,[sigh] I wish there were.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.07,0:08:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But to save our home, we\Nare willing to leave it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.50,0:08:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think you'll have to!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.87,0:08:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,My spell isn't finished yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.27,0:08:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but I think we can send The\NPony of Shadows to limbo
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.44,0:08:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,without all of you\Nhaving to go as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.74,0:08:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,While I appreciate your\Nenthusiasm, Twilight,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.98,0:08:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,this is hardly the time to take\Nrisks on half-baked spells.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.62,0:08:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Begging your pardon,\NMr. The Bearded.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.89,0:08:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But Twilight doesn't\Ndo anything half-way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.93,0:08:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially not magic!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.63,0:08:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Seriously! She got her wings by\Nfinishing one of your spells.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.20,0:08:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you'll find her\Nwork is worth reading
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.27,0:08:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,before you dismiss\Nit out of hoof!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.10,0:08:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm hm!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.64,0:09:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,While it is an\Nunconventional approach,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.21,0:09:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe it could work.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.04,0:09:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.18,0:09:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose there\Nis a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.85,0:09:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But we still have no idea\Nwhere to find the villain.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.83,0:09:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe we should try there?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.60,0:09:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The Hollow Shades.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.37,0:09:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I think a branch of the\NApple family lives there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.97,0:09:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They'd have to be\Npretty distant.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.81,0:09:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The Hollow Shades was\Nabandoned eons ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.14,0:09:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm, that's odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.68,0:09:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The only time the map's called\Nall of us to one place
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.25,0:09:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,was Starlight's village.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.05,0:09:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's like a\Nsuper-villain tracker!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.42,0:09:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,No offence.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.62,0:09:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think the map could\Nbe trying to tell us
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.46,0:09:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,where the Pony of Shadows is?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.96,0:09:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.96,0:09:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The Tree of Harmony acting to\Nprotect the light of the realm....
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.30,0:09:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, a good thought, Twilight.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.93,0:10:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I will make my\Nnotes on this spell.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.70,0:10:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready yourselves for battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.54,0:10:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, I know I'm not as\Nexperienced as all of you,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.51,0:10:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,but is banishment\Nreally the only option?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.28,0:10:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's been a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.31,0:10:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe the Pony of\NShadows is ready to talk?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.55,0:10:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I doubt we can save our\Nhomeland with a conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.22,0:10:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But we could try.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.62,0:10:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Starlight, I'm sure Starswirl\Nand the others did try.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.46,0:10:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pony of Shadows was not\Ninterested in reconciliation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.59,0:10:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Once a villain,\Nalways a villain.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.23,0:10:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Twilight? Sunburst?\NWould you accompany me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.53,0:10:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish to refine this\Nspell for our use.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.14,0:10:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Come! We must prepare\Nfor the struggle ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.34,0:10:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,[sigh] I know Starswirl\Nis a great wizard,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.48,0:10:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but this whole\Nplan seems... wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.98,0:10:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The map's only ever sent us\Nto solve friendship problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.12,0:10:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe so, but the\NPony of Shadows
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.35,0:10:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't really seem like the\Nfriendship type.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.39,0:10:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.39,0:10:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't know\Nanything about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.43,0:11:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Nopony does.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.80,0:11:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not entirely true.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.87,0:11:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You all knew the Pony of Shadows\Nbefore he became what he is now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.74,0:11:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You must've been friends..
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.41,0:11:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.85,0:11:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The tale of our\Nrift is a sad one.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.53,0:11:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Rockhoof:{\i1} Stygian was a pony{\i0}\N{\i1} like the rest of us,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.04,0:11:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}though more scholar than hero.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.97,0:11:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} He recognized our{\i0}\N{\i1} emerging world{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.81,0:11:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} would need champions{\i0}\N{\i1} to defend it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.53,0:12:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Flash Magnus:{\i1} He may have{\i0}\N{\i1} gathered us together,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.73,0:12:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} but he, himself was just{\i0}\N{\i1} an ordinary unicorn{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.80,0:12:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} who soon grew jealous{\i0}\N{\i1} of our abilities.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.87,0:12:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Mistmane:{\i1} He stole objects{\i0}\N{\i1} from each of us ...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.61,0:12:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} artifacts to use in a spell.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.94,0:12:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Meadowbrook:{\i1} And we cast{\i0}\N{\i1} him out for it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.78,0:12:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Somnambula:{\i1} We always{\i0}\N{\i1} thought he'd return{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.45,0:12:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} and seek forgiveness.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.39,0:12:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But when we saw him again, his{\i0}\N{\i1} heart was bent on revenge.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.86,0:12:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} He dashed even my{\i0}\N{\i1} hope of saving him.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.06,0:12:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But why did he steal\Nthe artifacts from you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.57,0:12:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,No doubt it was an enchantment\Nto take our powers for himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.10,0:12:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.51,0:12:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That looks like a lot of work.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.78,0:13:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It is what must be done\Nand it would be best
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.18,0:13:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,if we were not disturbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.68,0:13:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Starlight, but\Nwe can't stop to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.09,0:13:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The stakes are too\Nhigh and we have to...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.66,0:13:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,banish Stygian to limbo.\NI get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.26,0:13:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, who?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.26,0:13:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Stygian was the name the\NPony of Shadows gave up
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.00,0:13:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,when he turned to darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.00,0:13:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm just trying\Nto figure out why.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.73,0:13:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Envy. He wanted more\Npower than he had
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.24,0:13:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and that desire led\Nhim down a path
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.27,0:13:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,from which there is no return.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.57,0:13:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I know from experience\Nthat's not always true.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.58,0:13:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,When the map called\Nyou six to my village,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.64,0:13:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it was for a\Nfriendship problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.31,0:13:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure this is different?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.28,0:13:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.98,0:13:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Stygian wants to destroy all\Nthat is good in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.45,0:13:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way to\Nbefriend a pony like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.86,0:13:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess I'm lucky your\Nidol wasn't around
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.93,0:13:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,when you decided to\Nbe my friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.09,0:13:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I might've been\Nbanished to limbo too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.24,0:13:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Somnambula: I am glad we\Nhave the chance to see
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.71,0:14:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,what has grown from our\Nefforts so long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.28,0:14:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems a shame\Nto harm it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.15,0:14:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,A necessary sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.75,0:14:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,With the elements' power,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.85,0:14:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,we will bind the Pony\Nof Shadows in limbo.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.95,0:14:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And thanks to Twilight,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.29,0:14:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,we will remain to watch\Nover the realm ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.53,0:14:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, how do we use them?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.44,0:14:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you--Oh. I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.17,0:14:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They simply work for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.51,0:14:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The elements are\Nattuned to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.18,0:14:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We must use their\Nmagic in pairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.25,0:14:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,No problem!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.55,0:14:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We're used to banishing\Nevil before breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.28,0:14:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And it'll be an honor to\Nsave Equestria with y'all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.22,0:14:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I really hope Twilight\Nknows what she's doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.86,0:14:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember reading\Nanything that said
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.16,0:15:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the Hollow Shades\Nwas like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.80,0:15:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... the Pony of Shadows\Nmust have twisted it
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.40,0:15:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to his purposes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.77,0:15:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,[evil laugh]\NPrepare yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.68,0:15:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.28,0:15:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Stygian! Show\Nyourself and face us!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.55,0:15:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,[evil laughter]\N[rumbling]
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.80,0:15:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I definitely would have\Nremembered reading about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.14,0:15:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to the Well of Shade!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.68,0:15:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,When you turned your backs on\Nme, I discovered this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.79,0:15:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The darkness spoke to me of\Na power beyond any
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.56,0:15:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I could imagine and I listened.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.93,0:16:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The shadow and I became one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.43,0:16:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon all of the realm\Nwill be the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.83,0:16:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Then all ponies will\Nfeel the despair I did
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.63,0:16:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,when you cast me out!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.64,0:16:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We did\Nwhat we had to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.47,0:16:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You tried to steal our\Npowers for yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.18,0:16:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,No! It was you who were selfish!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.78,0:16:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And now you will pay!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.95,0:16:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you still sure this\Nisn't a friendship problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.75,0:16:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.49,0:16:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Open the portal...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.92,0:16:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,NOW!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.94,0:16:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,No! You will not\Ntrap me again!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.91,0:16:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Twilight! Push him in!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.28,0:16:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.51,0:16:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,There's... a pony in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.76,0:17:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.72,0:17:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Stygian?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.29,0:17:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I was, once.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.89,0:17:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Until my friends betrayed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.36,0:17:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But Starswirl says\Nyou betrayed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.83,0:17:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You wanted their magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.50,0:17:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,No! I wanted\Ntheir respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.80,0:17:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I brought them\Ntogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.17,0:17:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I planned strategy and\NI read all I could
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.21,0:17:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,about the beasts we faced.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.84,0:17:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But I didn't have\Nmagic or strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.18,0:17:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So nopony ever noticed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.65,0:17:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to Ponehenge to make my\Nown copies of the artifacts.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.25,0:17:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,With them, I thought I\Ncould be a Pillar too!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.62,0:17:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And stand by their\Nside in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.02,0:17:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I never wanted to\Nsteal their power.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.99,0:17:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But instead of sharing\Nand letting me help,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.59,0:17:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,my friends threw me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.53,0:17:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So I became stronger\Nthan any of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.03,0:17:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The darkness welcomed me\Nwhen no pony would.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.90,0:17:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I will do what I\Nmust to protect it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.54,0:17:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all a\Nmisunderstanding!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.54,0:17:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If the Pillars\Nknew how you felt,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.34,0:17:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure they wouldn't have\Nturned their backs on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.91,0:17:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The shadow isn't\Nwho you really are.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.31,0:18:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me help you\Nbe Stygian again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.41,0:18:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if my friends\Ndid still care,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.88,0:18:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,what makes you think you\Nhave the power to help me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.89,0:18:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Starlight: Because it's\Nwhat she does.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.82,0:18:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't so different from you\Nand Twilight helped me change.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.59,0:18:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If there's one pony in Equestria\Nthat can save a friendship,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.73,0:18:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it's her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.26,0:18:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I--I want to believe you....
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.63,0:18:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But the darkness\Nwill not be stopped!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.24,0:18:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Fight the darkness, Stygian!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.11,0:18:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.38,0:18:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Revenge isn't what you\Nwant, friendship is!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.92,0:18:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Twilight!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.96,0:18:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh.. the shadow won't let go of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.90,0:18:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants to stop, but\Nhe can't do it alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.00,0:18:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we must help him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.39,0:19:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,YEAH! It felt so good\Nto do that again!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.93,0:19:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Friendship power rush!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.93,0:19:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,WOO!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.63,0:19:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The elements!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.60,0:19:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,They didn't disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.07,0:19:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe because we used them\Nfor healing magic
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.41,0:19:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of banishing?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.94,0:19:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.48,0:19:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Long ago you needed\Nour help, Stygian,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.11,0:19:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,but instead of listening,\Nwe turned our backs on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.38,0:19:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Pride clouded my judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.92,0:19:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I owe you an apology.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.05,0:19:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for helping us see the\Nerrors of our ways, Twilight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.36,0:19:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems I never accounted\Nfor the magic of friendship.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.86,0:19:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Swirlstar.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.60,0:19:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Er... Starswirl!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.04,0:20:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,AHEM.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.37,0:20:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So apparently a conversation\Ncan save Equestria?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.31,0:20:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Something tells me I will be\Nmaking a lot of apologies today.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.65,0:20:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I simply cannot believe\Nhow tall you've gotten!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.92,0:20:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it has been\Nover a thousand years.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.36,0:20:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you stay here and\Nteach magic once again?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.10,0:20:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,My sister and I have such fond\Nmemories of your lessons.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.87,0:20:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as you don't ask for\Nthose essays we owed you
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.37,0:20:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,before you disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.80,0:20:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I am not certain Canterlot\Nis where I belong.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.04,0:20:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The realm has grown and I\Nbelieve I'll have a look around
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.61,0:20:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,before I settle\Nin any one place.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.98,0:20:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And I long to see what\Nhas become of my home.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.35,0:20:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe we all do.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.32,0:20:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I hope you will return to\NCanterlot on occasion
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.56,0:20:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and share the wisdom of\Nyour great experience
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.23,0:21:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,with the next\Ngeneration of ponies.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.83,0:21:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We would be honored, but\Nif it is wisdom you seek,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.00,0:21:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,look no further\Nthan your own pupil.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.43,0:21:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,She showed me that the\Npower of friendship
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.90,0:21:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is a magical force indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.27,0:21:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And that in turning\Naway from others,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.31,0:21:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you hurt yourself as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.88,0:21:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's funny. I thought\Nmeeting my idol
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.95,0:21:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,would give me all the\Nanswers I ever wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.25,0:21:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But instead, I forgot\Nwhat I already knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.42,0:21:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Good thing I had a student\Nof my own to remind me.
